postcontent:
Rare Ithaca Mag 10 Semi-Auto 10ga for sale/trade. Stock appears to be original furniture and in excellent shape with the IthacaGun butt pad.  The forearm is glossy checkered with minor dings on the bottom. This appears to be the Police version Roadblocker. Stainless steel gas recoil system. This is a factory modified version of the Ithaca Mag-10 with a shorter 21” barrel, and used to be issued to police officers to stop vehicles in their tracks.

Weighs about 11 lbs.  Incorporates a “countercoil” system which substantially reduces what would otherwise be an extreme recoil.  This shotgun has the vent rib option which was available in 1984-85. 

Each shot fired represents the equivalent of two 12-gauge shells loaded with the same type of buckshot, with only a relatively small increase in recoil and muzzle jump.  Great for turkey hunting, duck or goose or just playing.

Can also include 40 - 10 ga shotgun shells

$700 OBO cash or trade

title: For Sale:  FN Scar 17S (Heavy) with Primary Arms 1x6 Scope
postcontent:
Up for sale is an FN Scar 17S or sometimes called Scar Heavy.  It is in the Flat Dark Earth anodizing and coloration.  It is chambered in 7.62x51mm NATO but with also fire .308 Winchester.  The rifle has a piston operated system that is very reliable and I have never had any malfunctions.  The rifle also has ambidextrous features such as magazine release, selector switches, and the charging handle can be moved to either right or left side.  The rifle also has built in folding iron sights. The rifle comes with some added parts such as a Hogue overmolded pistol grip, Magpul Selectors, BCM Gunfighter fore grip, Impact Weapon Systems charging handle, Magpul FDE ladder covers.  The rifle is also outfitted with a Primary Arms 1x6 scope in an extended mount to allow easier charging of the weapon.  The scope has a BDC reticle to allow for holdovers out to 800 yards.  The scope also has wind holds and an auto ranging feature to allow you to make shots at unknown distances.  The rifle comes with an extra magazine giving a total of two 20 round magazines.  The rifle has 400 rounds of brass cases M80 7.62 NATO ammunition through it.  The rifle has been very accurate and has shot 1-1.5" groups at 100 yards thanks to the cold hammer forged 16.25" barrel.  The PwS FSC30 muzzle brake really helps with recoil and makes the rifle easy to shoot even for kids or women.

I am selling the rifle only because I am in the market for a new home or I would keep it because it is a joy to shoot and has been one of my favorite rifles.  I am asking $3200 OBO which you could not build this package for but I am open to offers (not ridiculous ones lol). No trades at this time. I am willing to ship to an out state buyer at their expense which can be negotiated. I will sell to a PA resident using a bill of sale which save you a couple hundred on taxes compared to buying new.

Speaking of HDMI, this receiver has 7 HDMI 1.4a inputs (6 back, 1 front) which provide 3D pass-through for Blu-ray and Broadcast content, and also supports Audio Return Channel. There are also 3 Y/Pr/Pb component inputs (capable of up to 1080i), 1 D-Sub (15pin) VGA input, 4 S-Video inputs, 4 RCA composite inputs, 3 coaxial digital inputs, 2 optical digital inputs, and 8 analog stereo RCA inputs.

Handling all the video from the many analog and digital inputs is Furoudja DCDi Cinema video Processor. The Furoudja DCDi upconverts and deinterlaces all signals to a native 1080p (24fps or 60fps) resolution, but does not have ISF Certified Calibration Controls. The dual HDMI 1.4a outs are also a nice feature, especially for those alternating between both a flat screen and a projection setup.

With Windows 7 and DNLA 1.5 Certification, the DTR-40.2 is also ready to stream music from the internet and on your home's broadband network. Using the unit's Ethernet jack to connect to the internet, users can enjoy Pandora, vTuner, Napster, Mediafly, Rhapsody, and may others. This receiver is also HD Radio and Sirius Satellite Radio ready.

The Integra DTR-40.2 is a very capable mid-level entry into the world of THX certification and 7.2 channel surround sound. The DTR-40.2 is available online and in local retailers for around $1,000.00.

I am asking $500 OBO for this completely refurbished unit. It was just returned by Integra after a full refurbish but I no longer need it. Willing to meet in/around The Woodlands/Magnolia/Conroe areas.

title: For Sale/Trade:  USED - Beretta U22 NEOS
postcontent:
U22 Neos: Today's Best Plinking Rimfire Pistol
 
Designed and manufactured in the USA, the new U22 Neos is a single-action .22 LR caliber plinking semiauto pistol. Although designed with the entry-level pistol shooter in mind, it is also ideal for training and can be adapted to the needs of experienced users. Its modular construction makes it easy to modify with a variety of options and accessories, while still being affordable both as a base pistol and as a fully-accessorized system.
 
 
Cool, Futuristic Design
 
Even while designing a plinking pistol to be used for informal shooting, Beretta did not cut corners. The lines of the Neos bear the unmistakable flavor of renown Italian designer Giugiaro--the same mind behind several of our most attractive offerings. The result is a sleek and ergonomic rimfire pistol that feels as good in the hands as it pleases the eyes.
 
 
Fully-Modular Construction
 
The Neos is constructed of five modular parts that may be easily disassembled and reassembled without any tools. The ergonomic grips are constructed of super-durable fiberglass-reinforced technopolymer with non-slip inserts for a comfortable and warm hold. The barrel is available either in the classic Beretta blue finish, or in stainless steel ("Inox"), to satisfy the tastes of every shooter. Most of these elements may be replaced with the rich assortment of accessories that is available for this fun .22 semiauto.
 
 
High Performance
 
Reliable, durable, easy to maintain and remarkably accurate, the Neos features an integral rail that accepts Weaver-style scope mounts as well as a fully-adjustable target rear sight. The firearm is also equipped with a cocked firing pin indicator at the rear of the pistol. The single stack, 10-round stainless-steel magazine features an easy-grip knob that allows you to compress the spring from outside, thereby making loading extremely quick and easy. The ambidextrous manual safety can be engaged with the firing pin cocked or uncocked. If you are in the market for a superbly-engineered plinking or practice pistol, give the Neos a close look--it won't fail to surpass your expectations.

title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant Carbine / M-44 7.62 x 54
postcontent:
(The Rifle)
Unissued - Mosin Nagant M-44 Carbine Rifle with folding bayonet, 7.62 x 54 caliber (roughly the equivalent of a 30.06 round).  This particular rifle is in excellent shape, with excellent wood (very smooth) and metal (hex receiver).  It was manufactured at the Tula arsenal plant in 1944.  The rifle has a clean, crisp bolt action (straight bolt), 5 round internal magazine, chambered in 7.62x54 which is powerful, cheap, and plentiful.  The bore, bolt, and barrel are clean, shiny, and function flawlessly.  I have shot less than 100 rounds thru this rifle.  Some believe it shoots more accurately with the bayonet extended.  It is very easy to disassemble and clean.  All matching serial numbers on bolt, barrel, receiver, and butt plate.  The rifle measures 40" inches from butt plate to muzzle.  The bayonet extended adds 12" inches.

When I purchased the rifle 9 years ago I looked all over for one manufactured at the Tula arsenal.  They were only made there part of one year - 1944.  The rifle was unissued during WWII and was packed away.  I had to do a lot of cleaning of the cosmoline (heavy grease).  The rifle was disassembled and the wood was lightly sanded to remove the dark cosmoline staining.  It was then restained, oiled, and waxed, before being reassembled.  

(The Ammo)
Available at Aimsurplus.com - Fantastic Surplus Bulgarian 7.62x54R ammunition. Manufactured in the late 1970s-mid-1980s, Features a copper washed full steel jacketed 147grn light ball steel core bullet. Packaged 440rds to a sealed "spam" can and 880rds per wooden crate.  ($99.95 plus $17.50 flat rate shipping for 440 rds).

(The history - cut and pasted)
The initial production of the M44 Carbine began in mid-late 1943 at the Izhevsk Armaments Factory. There were 50,000* of these carbines produced in 1943 and they were quickly deemed a success in field testing. Final approval was given and full production began in January of 1944. Production was undertaken at both the Izhevsk and Tula factories during the war, although the production at Tula was on a limited scale. To locate a Tula made M44 Carbine is quite a find for the Mosin collector, as the Tula production was on such a small scale that many had questioned if Tula was even involved in M44 Carbine manufacture.  We now know that Tula production of the M44 carbine only lasted a portion of one year, 1944. The exact number of Tula manufactured M44's is unknown but it is very clear that Tula production was quite small. While more examples of these have showed up in recent years, Tula produced carbines still need to be viewed as at least uncommon finds.  (This rifle is a Tula rifle and a rare find because of the hex receiver, and only being produced for part of 1944 - no other years at Tula).  

(The price)
I'm asking $250/obo for this rifle which is a fair price given it's rarity and condition.  Again, this is not an Izhevsk arsenal M-44 which were very plentiful.  I'm selling to add something different to my collection.  The rifle comes with a basic cleaning kit and issued sling.  Sorry ...... armlist only allowed the one picture.  Although the 20 or so pictures I have don't do it justice.   $250/obo  Call or text Al at REDACTED.
